Package EnchantmentOrder

package EnchantmentOrder
  • Class
    Description
    BinaryTree
    The underlying tree structure of a search result, it stores a reference to the result data after constructor, buildTree(): Node, build the tree structure for later traversal, parseTree(inputHashMap): Integer, assign the data to all the tree nodes, traversal(node, callback): Boolean, post-order traversal and callback non leaf node
    BinaryTreeOptimization
    static class of searching the optimal order
    EnchantmentMap
    Utility class to: convert enchantment id from/to String and Integer, get the enchantment weight of a X level enchantment
    EnchantStep
    The function that is passed to tree traversal, invoke parse(Node) every non leaf node
    JSONLoader
    Utility to load json file
    Main
    Main Entry Point
    Node
    The Node Class that maintains the optimal combining structure, left, right: the items in anvil to be combined, value: object of NodeValue that stores the information of a tree node
    NodeValue
    Class that store information of a tree node, cost: the cost of enchantment weight, prior: the cost of prior work penalty, enchant: the mapping of id:lv of the enchantments of this node
    SearchResult
    A class that store the Search Result, Extends this class as you like
